1
00:03:41,320 --> 00:03:43,480
Dad, why are you driving so fast?

2
00:03:43,560 --> 00:03:45,960
I'm trying to drop you off
at school on time.

3
00:03:46,040 --> 00:03:48,080
We might end up at the hospital instead.

4
00:03:48,160 --> 00:03:52,960
As long as I breathe,
I won't let anything happen to you.

5
00:03:53,040 --> 00:03:54,240
You must graduate.

6
00:03:54,320 --> 00:03:55,480
Once you graduate,

7
00:03:55,560 --> 00:03:57,800
you're going to be the head mechanic.

8
00:03:57,880 --> 00:03:59,840
You have to make it, son.

9
00:04:10,960 --> 00:04:13,080
<i>Dao, you have beauty and brains.</i>

10
00:04:13,160 --> 00:04:14,960
<i>You're accepting the Honor Student Award</i>
<i>again today.</i>

11
00:04:15,040 --> 00:04:16,160
<i>- Excellent!</i>
<i>- Yes!</i>

12
00:04:16,240 --> 00:04:19,360
Buttering me up. Are you expecting me
to treat you to shabu-shabu?

13
00:04:19,959 --> 00:04:22,320
<i>We're looking forward</i>
<i>to meeting your parents.</i>

14
00:04:22,400 --> 00:04:25,760
<i>They're going to treat us</i>
<i>to a fantastic meal.</i>

15
00:04:25,840 --> 00:04:27,840
I'm afraid we can't have that.

16
00:04:28,360 --> 00:04:31,400
My parents are busy.

17
00:04:32,480 --> 00:04:34,480
They won't come to the ceremony.

18
00:04:52,280 --> 00:04:54,320
Make it to graduation.

19
00:04:54,400 --> 00:04:57,000
Apply for scholarships abroad.

20
00:04:57,600 --> 00:05:00,200
With a degree,
you'll be a respected mechanic.

21
00:05:00,280 --> 00:05:02,320
You'll have a respectable desk job.

22
00:05:02,400 --> 00:05:04,080
You won't drive a taxi like me.

23
00:05:04,160 --> 00:05:06,280
What's wrong with being a taxi driver?

24
00:05:06,360 --> 00:05:08,120
There's nothing wrong with it.

25
00:05:08,920 --> 00:05:14,280
Actually, I am proud
that my dad is a taxi driver.

26
00:05:15,600 --> 00:05:17,560
You're sugarcoating it.

27
00:05:19,400 --> 00:05:22,160
People only respect money.

28
00:05:22,760 --> 00:05:25,200
Trust me. Finish your school.

29
00:05:25,800 --> 00:05:29,040
Become the head mechanic
and rake in the cash.

30
00:05:29,120 --> 00:05:32,840
When you have a wife,
she won't have to be ashamed of you.

31
00:05:35,120 --> 00:05:37,680
I don't need a woman
who judges a book by its cover.

32
00:05:38,800 --> 00:05:41,880
I will pick the one who loves me as I am.

33
00:05:44,160 --> 00:05:45,000
Fine.

34
00:06:52,680 --> 00:06:54,840
TAXI SERVICE

35
00:07:05,280 --> 00:07:06,920
I'm heading to work, son.

36
00:07:07,640 --> 00:07:09,640
Stay focused.

37
00:07:10,560 --> 00:07:11,440
All right, Dad.

38
00:07:17,600 --> 00:07:19,560
PATHUMTHANI TECHNICAL COLLEGE

39
00:07:25,480 --> 00:07:26,760
Sorry, Dad.

40
00:07:27,720 --> 00:07:29,560
I don't want to build any buildings.

41
00:07:30,480 --> 00:07:31,880
I want to make music.

42
00:07:42,320 --> 00:07:43,160
Petch!

43
00:07:45,200 --> 00:07:46,120
What's wrong?

44
00:07:46,720 --> 00:07:48,480
We have a band competition today.

45
00:07:48,560 --> 00:07:51,000
We should be preparing our instruments.

46
00:07:51,080 --> 00:07:54,960
We cannot do anything.
Our bass player is getting beaten up.

47
00:07:55,040 --> 00:07:57,240
You mean Boy? What's happening?

48
00:07:57,320 --> 00:07:58,400
It was Joe.

49
00:07:58,480 --> 00:08:01,160
He beat up Boy
so that he would win the competition.

50
00:08:01,240 --> 00:08:02,920
Such a cheap shot. Where's Joe?

51
00:08:03,000 --> 00:08:03,840
At the back.

52
00:08:03,920 --> 00:08:05,040
- Go.
- Go.

53
00:08:10,880 --> 00:08:13,160
Joe! Stop!

54
00:08:16,440 --> 00:08:17,800
Your dad came to rescue you.

55
00:08:19,040 --> 00:08:20,040
But I think

56
00:08:20,640 --> 00:08:21,880
he doesn't have the guts.

57
00:08:21,960 --> 00:08:24,640
I'm not sure about that.

58
00:08:25,520 --> 00:08:26,440
But surely, I have talent.

59
00:08:27,400 --> 00:08:29,400
I won't use a cheap shot like you all did.

60
00:08:29,920 --> 00:08:30,880
He's right.

61
00:08:31,400 --> 00:08:33,159
- You all suck.
- Shut up!

62
00:08:33,840 --> 00:08:35,120
Beat the hell out of them!

63
00:09:07,040 --> 00:09:08,000
Petch, watch out!

64
00:09:18,520 --> 00:09:19,720
Stop!

65
00:09:20,600 --> 00:09:22,960
I won't be easy on you.

66
00:09:24,280 --> 00:09:25,120
Joe.

67
00:09:25,200 --> 00:09:26,200
You must pay for this!

68
00:09:26,280 --> 00:09:29,960
- No!
- Dam! Easy, Dam!

69
00:09:38,880 --> 00:09:40,520
I don't like an unfair fight.

70
00:09:41,440 --> 00:09:42,360
That's not what real men do.

71
00:09:43,400 --> 00:09:44,440
You and I,

72
00:09:45,520 --> 00:09:47,440
we'd better compete on stage.

73
00:09:48,880 --> 00:09:50,480
Let's have a fair fight

74
00:09:53,080 --> 00:09:54,080
like real men.

75
00:10:00,400 --> 00:10:02,160
The concert is about to start.

76
00:10:02,240 --> 00:10:04,640
The doors will open
for the audience in a minute.

77
00:10:06,600 --> 00:10:10,000
Come witness the champion

78
00:10:10,080 --> 00:10:12,520
of the Mechanic Students'
Battle of the Bands!

79
00:10:12,600 --> 00:10:17,000
Without further ado, please welcome

80
00:10:17,600 --> 00:10:21,600
In-see!

81
00:10:22,200 --> 00:10:24,760
Louder!

82
00:10:33,920 --> 00:10:36,000
There is no miracle in my life.

83
00:10:37,080 --> 00:10:38,880
My life is full of dreams.

84
00:10:38,960 --> 00:10:41,720
And no matter how hard my dream is,

85
00:10:42,520 --> 00:10:43,920
I will make it come true.

86
00:11:23,680 --> 00:11:25,840
<i>Gazing at the sky</i>

87
00:11:26,920 --> 00:11:29,400
<i>Wishing for a brighter day</i>

88
00:11:30,000 --> 00:11:33,120
<i>Let the memories of the past</i>
<i>Simply fade away</i>

89
00:11:33,200 --> 00:11:37,280
<i>Today is brand new</i>

90
00:11:37,360 --> 00:11:39,640
<i>And as the sun</i>

91
00:11:40,520 --> 00:11:41,800
<i>Breaks through the rain</i>

92
00:11:41,880 --> 00:11:43,080
Freaking lame.

93
00:11:43,160 --> 00:11:46,640
<i>A rainbow weaves its colors</i>
<i>To chase the dark away</i>

94
00:11:46,720 --> 00:11:50,200
<i>With clarity in my eyes</i>

95
00:11:50,280 --> 00:11:52,520
<i>I finally find my way</i>

96
00:11:58,000 --> 00:12:00,600
JUDGES

97
00:12:08,240 --> 00:12:09,240
Stay on tempo.

98
00:12:19,880 --> 00:12:21,280
- Sir.
- Yes?

99
00:12:21,360 --> 00:12:23,160
Can I borrow your megaphone, please?

100
00:12:25,160 --> 00:12:28,320
<i>Before exhaustion takes its toll</i>

101
00:12:28,400 --> 00:12:31,960
<i>Before time slips beyond control</i>

102
00:12:32,040 --> 00:12:35,280
<i>I've learned that when I stop searching</i>

103
00:12:35,360 --> 00:12:38,760
<i>Everything finds its place</i>

104
00:12:38,840 --> 00:12:41,880
<i>Before exhaustion takes its toll</i>

105
00:12:41,960 --> 00:12:45,920
<i>Let the pain affirm</i>
<i>That life is simply this way</i>

106
00:12:46,000 --> 00:12:48,840
<i>When I stopped the chase</i>

107
00:12:48,920 --> 00:12:51,520
<i>The clouds finally part</i>

108
00:12:51,600 --> 00:12:53,480
<i>And sorrow lifts from my heart</i>

109
00:13:01,200 --> 00:13:03,280
Our Petch is the real deal!

110
00:13:03,360 --> 00:13:05,680
No one can stop you from singing.

111
00:13:06,200 --> 00:13:07,680
- You're the man, bro!
- Guys.

112
00:13:07,760 --> 00:13:09,280
Stop flattering me.

113
00:13:09,800 --> 00:13:12,360
I just thought
that once I get up on stage,

114
00:13:12,880 --> 00:13:15,240
I must finish my song
no matter what happens.

115
00:13:15,320 --> 00:13:16,320
Damn right, you did.

116
00:13:17,880 --> 00:13:19,360
The power went out all of a sudden.

117
00:13:19,440 --> 00:13:22,400
I think some shameless pricks

118
00:13:23,000 --> 00:13:24,400
intentionally cut the power off.

119
00:13:24,480 --> 00:13:25,480
What are you talking about?

120
00:13:25,560 --> 00:13:28,160
- About you pricks!
- Dam, easy!

121
00:13:28,800 --> 00:13:29,840
Dam, enough.

122
00:13:30,920 --> 00:13:31,960
Petch.

123
00:13:32,480 --> 00:13:35,840
You shouldn't have let these pricks
stab you in the back.

124
00:13:36,640 --> 00:13:38,840
Hear me out, Joe.

125
00:13:38,920 --> 00:13:40,760
The more you try to bring Petch down,

126
00:13:41,440 --> 00:13:43,000
the more he is going to shine.

127
00:13:44,800 --> 00:13:46,280
Thunder!

128
00:13:46,800 --> 00:13:48,200
Stand by.

129
00:13:48,280 --> 00:13:49,760
Watch us

130
00:13:50,640 --> 00:13:53,040
and learn what failure tastes like.

131
00:13:54,200 --> 00:13:55,040
Oh, wow.

132
00:13:57,680 --> 00:13:59,280
"Learn what failure tastes like."

133
00:13:59,800 --> 00:14:01,560
The next band is

134
00:14:01,640 --> 00:14:03,920
Thunder!

135
00:14:23,200 --> 00:14:26,400
<i>I know you're cruel</i>

136
00:14:26,480 --> 00:14:30,920
<i>Yet I find myself giving in</i>

137
00:14:31,760 --> 00:14:35,560
<i>I know you'll break your word</i>

138
00:14:35,640 --> 00:14:39,680
<i>But I'm still stuck on you</i>

139
00:14:39,760 --> 00:14:43,560
<i>Just one look into your eyes</i>

140
00:14:43,640 --> 00:14:46,400
<i>And my heart…</i>

141
00:14:46,480 --> 00:14:49,680
Now, it's the time
we've all been looking forward to.

142
00:14:51,120 --> 00:14:56,160
The winner announcement.

143
00:14:56,240 --> 00:14:59,120
The Best Band of the Year

144
00:15:00,720 --> 00:15:01,560
goes

145
00:15:02,600 --> 00:15:03,560
to…

146
00:15:07,240 --> 00:15:09,200
In-see!

147
00:15:09,280 --> 00:15:10,640
Yes!

148
00:15:10,720 --> 00:15:12,280
- Oh, wow!
- Yes!

149
00:15:14,600 --> 00:15:17,480
Yes!

150
00:15:17,560 --> 00:15:19,000
- Yes!
- Yes!

151
00:15:23,040 --> 00:15:25,400
Yes!

152
00:15:30,880 --> 00:15:33,760
After all those dirty tricks,
they still won?

153
00:15:34,280 --> 00:15:35,680
Shut up, Bank!

154
00:15:41,120 --> 00:15:42,520
This isn't over.

155
00:15:43,240 --> 00:15:44,760
Next time, it will be my turn.

156
00:15:54,240 --> 00:15:56,240
Yes!

157
00:15:56,320 --> 00:15:58,520
Yes!

158
00:15:58,600 --> 00:16:02,160
This is the taste of victory.

159
00:16:03,640 --> 00:16:04,560
Petch.

160
00:16:04,640 --> 00:16:05,960
What's wrong, man?

161
00:16:06,040 --> 00:16:07,240
Aren't you happy?

162
00:16:11,680 --> 00:16:12,840
I am happy.

163
00:16:15,480 --> 00:16:16,520
But…

164
00:16:17,120 --> 00:16:19,160
But? But what?

165
00:16:21,200 --> 00:16:23,280
My dad doesn't approve of me
playing music.

166
00:16:23,360 --> 00:16:27,400
If he knew I had a band,
he would beat me for sure.

167
00:16:28,520 --> 00:16:29,360
Petch.

168
00:16:30,440 --> 00:16:31,720
If you don't tell

169
00:16:32,240 --> 00:16:33,200
and I don't tell,

170
00:16:34,040 --> 00:16:36,080
your dad won't know.

171
00:16:39,720 --> 00:16:41,200
But it's frustrating.

172
00:16:42,640 --> 00:16:44,080
I don't want to lie.

173
00:17:02,400 --> 00:17:03,240
What's on your mind?

174
00:17:03,840 --> 00:17:04,760
Nothing.

175
00:17:06,000 --> 00:17:07,800
I was just curious.

176
00:17:08,640 --> 00:17:09,599
About what?

177
00:17:10,440 --> 00:17:11,280
I mean…

178
00:17:12,960 --> 00:17:15,079
Do those who were born with a silver spoon

179
00:17:16,359 --> 00:17:19,280
have conflicts with their parents
like us poor kids?

180
00:17:19,800 --> 00:17:20,720
What?

181
00:17:26,280 --> 00:17:29,480
The Honor Student Award goes to

182
00:17:30,600 --> 00:17:32,680
Ms. Natedao Akkarangkul,

183
00:17:32,760 --> 00:17:36,000
Grade 12, Classroom 1.

184
00:18:01,920 --> 00:18:03,320
One more picture.

185
00:18:04,560 --> 00:18:06,480
- Beautiful. One more picture.
- Okay.

186
00:18:10,600 --> 00:18:11,680
Dao.

187
00:18:13,280 --> 00:18:14,560
It's okay.

188
00:18:14,640 --> 00:18:17,440
Even though your parents didn't come,
you still have us.

189
00:18:18,240 --> 00:18:19,320
That's right.

190
00:18:19,400 --> 00:18:21,760
Would you like to take a photo
with my parents?

191
00:18:21,840 --> 00:18:23,120
I don't want to bother them.

192
00:18:23,640 --> 00:18:25,360
I can be by myself.

193
00:18:25,440 --> 00:18:26,800
You two don't have to worry.

194
00:18:28,840 --> 00:18:30,960
Okay, we're heading in.

195
00:18:31,040 --> 00:18:31,880
Okay.

196
00:18:35,680 --> 00:18:36,760
Dao.

197
00:18:40,880 --> 00:18:42,080
Dad, Mom.

198
00:18:44,040 --> 00:18:46,520
Hi. What brings you two here?

199
00:18:46,600 --> 00:18:50,880
Your mother's friend
is the editor of an online magazine.

200
00:18:50,960 --> 00:18:53,240
He wants to write an article
about our family.

201
00:18:53,320 --> 00:18:55,400
So, we changed our flight to be here.

202
00:18:56,400 --> 00:19:00,880
Too bad we couldn't make it
when Dao received the award.

203
00:19:01,760 --> 00:19:03,120
Let me see, sweetheart.

204
00:19:05,480 --> 00:19:08,680
The certificate would suffice, honey.

205
00:19:08,760 --> 00:19:10,400
Perfect for the article.

206
00:19:10,480 --> 00:19:11,600
Yes.

207
00:19:12,120 --> 00:19:13,560
Perfect for digital content.

208
00:19:15,120 --> 00:19:16,280
Hello, sir.

209
00:19:16,360 --> 00:19:17,400
Hello, sir.

210
00:19:17,480 --> 00:19:18,480
- Hi.
- Hi.

211
00:19:19,080 --> 00:19:19,920
Hi.

212
00:19:20,440 --> 00:19:23,440
Dao, honey, we'd better move that way.

213
00:19:23,520 --> 00:19:24,400
That way, please.

214
00:19:24,480 --> 00:19:26,560
That way, please.
Dao, come on up, sweetie.

215
00:19:49,680 --> 00:19:52,360
Children are like modeling clay.

216
00:19:52,440 --> 00:19:57,240
It is all up to us, the parents,
on how we shape them.

217
00:19:58,040 --> 00:20:00,440
That's right.

218
00:20:00,520 --> 00:20:03,640
I planned her path before she was born.

219
00:20:03,720 --> 00:20:06,480
That's why the result is perfect.

220
00:20:08,040 --> 00:20:11,520
You're raising her as if you're planning
to build a tower, right?

221
00:20:12,360 --> 00:20:13,640
Probably yes.

222
00:20:17,240 --> 00:20:19,000
With the Honor Student Award,

223
00:20:19,080 --> 00:20:21,720
do you wish for any gifts
from your parents?

224
00:20:24,400 --> 00:20:26,360
I wish for…

225
00:20:26,440 --> 00:20:27,840
A new piano?

226
00:20:30,680 --> 00:20:33,040
She loves the piano.

227
00:20:33,640 --> 00:20:37,080
The one we have is quite small.

228
00:20:37,160 --> 00:20:41,720
So, we plan to buy her
a new piano as a gift.

229
00:20:43,240 --> 00:20:44,720
<i>You'll have a grand piano.</i>

230
00:20:44,800 --> 00:20:47,080
<i>You can rehearse for the contest.</i>

231
00:20:47,160 --> 00:20:50,720
Any size or any price.

232
00:21:08,800 --> 00:21:09,680
Miss.

233
00:21:10,840 --> 00:21:12,520
Is everything all right, miss?

234
00:21:15,440 --> 00:21:18,200
I've never seen you
being aggressive with the piano.

235
00:21:18,280 --> 00:21:19,840
What song was it?

236
00:21:20,840 --> 00:21:22,640
The song is "Rattle the Cage."

237
00:21:23,160 --> 00:21:24,800
Here is your orange juice.

238
00:21:24,880 --> 00:21:28,160
The next schedule will be
physics and chemistry.

239
00:21:28,240 --> 00:21:29,520
Miss!

240
00:21:50,080 --> 00:21:53,120
<i>I live in an enormous house.</i>

241
00:21:53,200 --> 00:21:57,000
<i>I have a car. I have a piano.</i>
<i>I have everything.</i>

242
00:21:58,240 --> 00:21:59,960
<i>But I feel alone.</i>

243
00:22:01,080 --> 00:22:03,280
<i>If only I could make a wish,</i>

244
00:22:04,200 --> 00:22:07,120
<i>I would wish for someone</i>
<i>who truly understands me.</i>

245
00:22:19,240 --> 00:22:20,440
Yes, Uncle.

246
00:22:20,520 --> 00:22:22,880
I'm working on
the pub's accounts right now.

247
00:22:22,960 --> 00:22:25,000
<i>It's very late. Have you gone home yet?</i>

248
00:22:25,840 --> 00:22:28,800
I'm planning to hold
a meeting with the staff

249
00:22:28,880 --> 00:22:31,520
to brainstorm promotions for next month.

250
00:22:31,600 --> 00:22:34,240
<i>That is very dedicated of you. Good job.</i>

251
00:22:35,600 --> 00:22:37,640
I'm just following your example, Uncle.

252
00:22:37,720 --> 00:22:39,320
You're the one who taught me,

253
00:22:39,400 --> 00:22:41,880
"If we want to get rich,
we have to work hard."

254
00:22:41,960 --> 00:22:43,240
<i>Exactly.</i>

255
00:22:43,320 --> 00:22:46,360
<i>In that case,</i>
<i>come into the office tomorrow.</i>

256
00:22:46,440 --> 00:22:48,480
<i>Join the meeting</i>
<i>for "The Rock Concert" project.</i>

257
00:22:48,560 --> 00:22:51,400
Will do, Uncle. Goodbye.

258
00:22:54,880 --> 00:22:56,120
Why did he have to call?

259
00:22:56,200 --> 00:22:57,400
So damn annoying.

260
00:23:03,680 --> 00:23:06,720
Don't be so grumpy, Papa Ake.

261
00:23:07,440 --> 00:23:08,880
Mud.

262
00:23:08,960 --> 00:23:10,320
Go wait outside.

263
00:23:11,640 --> 00:23:12,480
Yes, sir.

264
00:23:13,320 --> 00:23:14,160
Hey.

265
00:23:15,520 --> 00:23:16,400
Joe.

266
00:23:17,120 --> 00:23:17,960
Take it easy

267
00:23:18,560 --> 00:23:20,120
or you will pass out.

268
00:23:20,720 --> 00:23:22,120
Don't you get it?

269
00:23:22,200 --> 00:23:24,720
He drinks because he lost to Petch.

270
00:23:25,320 --> 00:23:27,840
With all our dirty tricks, we still lost.

271
00:23:27,920 --> 00:23:28,760
Asshole!

272
00:23:29,360 --> 00:23:31,040
Want my foot instead of the booze?

273
00:23:33,000 --> 00:23:34,640
Get this in your skull.

274
00:23:35,680 --> 00:23:36,760
I'm not losing to Petch.

275
00:23:37,360 --> 00:23:39,120
- I will win!
- Hey!

276
00:23:39,200 --> 00:23:40,320
Hey!

277
00:23:44,280 --> 00:23:45,600
Asshole!

278
00:23:49,720 --> 00:23:51,200
You're so tough, huh?

279
00:23:53,840 --> 00:23:56,000
Stop! Enough!

280
00:24:00,040 --> 00:24:01,400
Stop!

281
00:24:01,920 --> 00:24:02,920
Want to get some?

282
00:24:06,440 --> 00:24:07,360
Stop!

283
00:24:13,840 --> 00:24:14,880
Get in!

284
00:24:15,800 --> 00:24:16,800
Sir.

285
00:24:17,520 --> 00:24:19,160
This one caused trouble.

286
00:24:19,240 --> 00:24:21,040
The damage costs 50,000 baht.

287
00:24:21,560 --> 00:24:22,680
Who is he?

288
00:24:23,400 --> 00:24:24,360
Your dad, perhaps.

289
00:24:24,440 --> 00:24:26,800
His dad?

290
00:24:27,320 --> 00:24:28,720
Let go of me!

291
00:24:28,800 --> 00:24:32,400
Or I will report to the police
that you allow minors in the pub.

292
00:24:32,480 --> 00:24:35,080
When it gets on the news,
the pub will be shut down.

293
00:24:41,880 --> 00:24:42,760
The first shot

294
00:24:44,280 --> 00:24:45,720
was for fun.

295
00:24:46,320 --> 00:24:47,760
But the next one

296
00:24:48,600 --> 00:24:49,960
will be for your brain.

297
00:24:50,040 --> 00:24:51,480
Please don't shoot me.

298
00:24:52,560 --> 00:24:53,440
I'm sorry.

299
00:24:54,040 --> 00:24:54,880
I'm begging you.

300
00:24:57,200 --> 00:24:58,320
Idiot!

301
00:24:58,400 --> 00:24:59,920
You're asking for it!

302
00:25:08,560 --> 00:25:09,880
I'm begging you.

303
00:25:11,040 --> 00:25:12,880
I would do anything.

304
00:25:15,880 --> 00:25:19,480
Then find me 100,000 baht.

305
00:25:20,160 --> 00:25:22,000
But he said it costs 50,000.

306
00:25:22,080 --> 00:25:23,280
Do you want to live?

307
00:25:24,080 --> 00:25:24,920
Do you?

308
00:25:27,320 --> 00:25:32,520
Find me 100,000 baht
by the end of the month

309
00:25:33,760 --> 00:25:34,640
or you'll be dead.

310
00:25:39,960 --> 00:25:41,000
Get lost!

311
00:25:44,360 --> 00:25:45,360
Go!

312
00:26:00,920 --> 00:26:01,760
Petch.

313
00:26:02,280 --> 00:26:04,480
Wake up, son. You'll be late for school.

314
00:26:04,560 --> 00:26:05,440
Petch?

315
00:26:09,880 --> 00:26:10,720
What?

316
00:26:11,240 --> 00:26:12,720
He woke up early.

317
00:26:14,360 --> 00:26:16,560
He didn't make the bed.

318
00:26:17,080 --> 00:26:18,560
He didn't close the window.

319
00:26:55,880 --> 00:27:00,560
<i>You are out of reach</i>

320
00:27:00,640 --> 00:27:06,080
<i>Is it a crime that I need you?</i>

321
00:27:08,000 --> 00:27:12,400
<i>Please let me know for sure</i>

322
00:27:13,000 --> 00:27:18,320
<i>That you're the one I've been waiting for</i>

323
00:27:18,920 --> 00:27:23,480
<i>How much longer can I bear this pain?</i>

324
00:27:24,880 --> 00:27:29,800
<i>How much longer must I wait in vain?</i>

325
00:27:30,960 --> 00:27:33,440
<i>I really don't know</i>

326
00:27:33,520 --> 00:27:36,920
<i>What move to make</i>

327
00:27:37,000 --> 00:27:42,360
<i>To end this heartache</i>
<i>And say that I love you</i>

328
00:27:42,960 --> 00:27:48,280
<i>I really don't know what move to make</i>

329
00:27:48,880 --> 00:27:55,680
<i>To end this heartache</i>
<i>And say that I love you</i>

330
00:28:02,360 --> 00:28:03,640
- See you, man.
- Okay.

331
00:28:03,720 --> 00:28:05,360
STATION 53

332
00:28:05,440 --> 00:28:06,560
Duean.

333
00:28:07,280 --> 00:28:09,080
I've finished my gig.

334
00:28:12,320 --> 00:28:14,120
Where are you taking my daughter?

335
00:28:15,040 --> 00:28:15,880
Dad.

336
00:28:18,800 --> 00:28:20,000
Nop!

337
00:28:20,840 --> 00:28:22,080
Nop!

338
00:28:23,120 --> 00:28:25,680
Dad, I'm begging you.

339
00:28:25,760 --> 00:28:26,800
Please let Nop go.

340
00:28:26,880 --> 00:28:30,600
Do you think
you can date a man with nothing?

341
00:28:30,680 --> 00:28:32,160
Dad.

342
00:28:32,240 --> 00:28:35,000
He's not rich, but he's a good man.

343
00:28:35,080 --> 00:28:36,120
Please let him go.

344
00:28:36,200 --> 00:28:37,160
Enough.

345
00:28:37,240 --> 00:28:38,480
Hey.

346
00:28:39,400 --> 00:28:40,880
Make him know his place.

347
00:28:41,840 --> 00:28:43,920
- Stay away from my daughter.
- Nop!

348
00:28:44,520 --> 00:28:46,840
- Nop!
- Go!

349
00:28:46,920 --> 00:28:49,000
Nop!

350
00:28:50,800 --> 00:28:51,840
Beat him!

351
00:29:01,280 --> 00:29:03,880
Let go of me!

352
00:29:06,280 --> 00:29:07,400
You ungrateful child!

353
00:29:08,000 --> 00:29:09,480
I will send you to live abroad!

354
00:29:09,560 --> 00:29:14,400
I don't want to! Dad!

355
00:29:26,080 --> 00:29:27,120
Duean.

356
00:29:27,720 --> 00:29:29,000
Nop.

357
00:29:38,000 --> 00:29:39,160
I think you should--

358
00:29:39,240 --> 00:29:40,280
Nop.

359
00:29:40,880 --> 00:29:42,880
Please don't tell me to go back home.

360
00:29:43,640 --> 00:29:47,120
I ran away because I've made my decision.

361
00:29:48,000 --> 00:29:49,160
Duean.

362
00:29:49,240 --> 00:29:51,560
Of course, money matters,

363
00:29:51,640 --> 00:29:53,760
but spending my life with you
matters more.

364
00:29:55,400 --> 00:29:57,280
I don't want you to live a tough life.

365
00:29:57,880 --> 00:29:59,520
Baby.

366
00:29:59,600 --> 00:30:01,800
Tough life won't scare me.

367
00:30:07,920 --> 00:30:08,800
Here.

368
00:30:09,560 --> 00:30:13,320
Just try your best to follow your dream

369
00:30:13,840 --> 00:30:15,880
and we'll start our new lives together.

370
00:30:19,480 --> 00:30:20,320
Duean.

371
00:30:27,080 --> 00:30:28,320
Thank you, Duean.

372
00:30:29,880 --> 00:30:31,000
Thank you so much.

373
00:30:36,080 --> 00:30:39,240
Give it back!

374
00:30:40,360 --> 00:30:41,720
Nop!

375
00:30:42,240 --> 00:30:43,640
Get inside, son!

376
00:30:48,440 --> 00:30:49,800
Let's go!

377
00:30:56,880 --> 00:30:57,720
Duean?

378
00:31:01,840 --> 00:31:03,160
Stay with me.

379
00:31:06,160 --> 00:31:07,920
I'll take you to the hospital.

380
00:31:08,440 --> 00:31:09,680
Stay with me.

381
00:31:12,520 --> 00:31:13,480
Please…

382
00:31:15,280 --> 00:31:17,440
take care of Petch.

383
00:31:18,160 --> 00:31:19,000
Duean?

384
00:31:22,000 --> 00:31:24,200
Duean.

385
00:31:24,280 --> 00:31:25,120
Duean!

386
00:31:30,640 --> 00:31:32,920
A poor musician like me…

387
00:31:39,400 --> 00:31:41,000
caused Duean's death.

388
00:31:48,120 --> 00:31:49,680
I won't allow Petch…

389
00:31:53,000 --> 00:31:54,880
to make the same mistake as mine.

390
00:32:02,280 --> 00:32:03,320
Dad.

391
00:32:03,400 --> 00:32:05,520
I bought you hot soy milk with <i>patongko</i>.

392
00:32:20,960 --> 00:32:21,800
What is this?

393
00:32:26,800 --> 00:32:30,040
Didn't I tell you to quit music?

394
00:32:30,120 --> 00:32:31,960
Why didn't you do as I said?

395
00:32:32,040 --> 00:32:34,000
Because you're being unreasonable.

396
00:32:34,080 --> 00:32:35,640
Why can't I play music?

397
00:32:35,720 --> 00:32:39,640
If you keep playing music,
what will happen to your studies?

398
00:32:39,720 --> 00:32:41,280
What would you do for a living?

399
00:32:42,360 --> 00:32:44,280
Musicians can be responsible
for themselves.

400
00:32:44,360 --> 00:32:45,880
I can take care of you too.

401
00:32:46,480 --> 00:32:47,720
It's an unstable career.

402
00:32:48,240 --> 00:32:50,240
It doesn't come with benefits.

403
00:32:50,320 --> 00:32:51,720
How could you say that?

404
00:32:51,800 --> 00:32:53,680
I'm trying to set you straight.

405
00:32:53,760 --> 00:32:58,400
Once your popularity is over,
you'll be nothing but a stray dog!

406
00:32:59,400 --> 00:33:00,520
That's not true.

407
00:33:00,600 --> 00:33:04,000
You used to be a musician.
You used to play guitar too.

408
00:33:28,320 --> 00:33:29,920
I learned the hard way

409
00:33:30,000 --> 00:33:31,840
that it's an unstable career.

410
00:33:31,920 --> 00:33:33,640
I could barely feed a family.

411
00:33:34,640 --> 00:33:36,400
I don't want you to be like me.

412
00:33:38,320 --> 00:33:39,800
Mark my words.

413
00:33:39,880 --> 00:33:41,800
If you don't quit music,

414
00:33:42,520 --> 00:33:44,120
you are no longer my son!

415
00:33:44,880 --> 00:33:45,720
Remember that!

416
00:34:08,159 --> 00:34:09,120
Petch.

417
00:34:09,199 --> 00:34:11,880
Come on, man.
Scolding is a love language for fathers.

418
00:34:11,960 --> 00:34:13,880
Do you think this is a joke?

419
00:34:13,960 --> 00:34:14,800
Hey.

420
00:34:14,880 --> 00:34:17,320
I told you not to bring the guitar home.

421
00:34:17,400 --> 00:34:18,520
Dam.

422
00:34:19,159 --> 00:34:20,719
I don't need more lecturing.

423
00:34:21,480 --> 00:34:23,480
Give all your money to me!

424
00:34:25,199 --> 00:34:26,679
If you don't want to get hurt,

425
00:34:27,360 --> 00:34:29,639
give it to me!

426
00:34:32,760 --> 00:34:33,920
What are you doing?

427
00:34:34,000 --> 00:34:35,440
None of your business.

428
00:34:36,800 --> 00:34:38,600
Pay and get lost!

429
00:34:39,239 --> 00:34:40,440
Go.

430
00:34:41,040 --> 00:34:42,639
Get lost.

431
00:34:42,719 --> 00:34:44,639
How can you shake down juniors like this?

432
00:34:45,159 --> 00:34:46,400
Give them back the money.

433
00:34:46,480 --> 00:34:47,719
A man with a good heart,

434
00:34:48,239 --> 00:34:49,320
but…

435
00:34:50,120 --> 00:34:51,239
Joe!

436
00:35:05,240 --> 00:35:06,680
Come here!

437
00:35:27,320 --> 00:35:28,160
Over there!

438
00:35:28,240 --> 00:35:29,640
Stop it!

439
00:35:29,720 --> 00:35:30,960
- Over there!
- Petch, stop!

440
00:35:34,440 --> 00:35:36,920
Sir! Petch was attacking me!

441
00:35:37,760 --> 00:35:39,600
He's lying.

442
00:35:39,680 --> 00:35:41,800
Quiet for now.

443
00:35:41,880 --> 00:35:43,920
You two, at the school director's office.

444
00:35:52,160 --> 00:35:55,560
You all should know
that we ban physical fights.

445
00:35:56,160 --> 00:35:57,840
I'm aware of that, sir.

446
00:35:57,920 --> 00:36:00,600
But I can't stand seeing Joe
bully the younger kids.

447
00:36:02,080 --> 00:36:03,560
He framed me.

448
00:36:04,160 --> 00:36:06,560
He just attacked out of the blue.

449
00:36:06,640 --> 00:36:07,640
Liar!

450
00:36:08,560 --> 00:36:11,200
He's lying, sir. I can be Petch's witness.

451
00:36:11,280 --> 00:36:14,240
Witness? You two are friends!
You're backing him up!

452
00:36:15,680 --> 00:36:18,240
All right, stop the argument right now.

453
00:36:19,360 --> 00:36:20,800
Sit down.

454
00:36:30,560 --> 00:36:31,640
Well,

455
00:36:31,720 --> 00:36:34,800
what's the progress
with the investigation?

456
00:36:35,400 --> 00:36:38,200
Did Joe really extort money
from younger students?

457
00:36:38,280 --> 00:36:39,680
No report at all.

458
00:36:39,760 --> 00:36:41,600
I tried asking them many times.

459
00:36:45,920 --> 00:36:48,200
Since there are no witnesses,

460
00:36:50,200 --> 00:36:51,680
you can't come up with more excuses.

461
00:36:57,400 --> 00:36:59,400
You are on probation.

462
00:37:00,880 --> 00:37:03,160
Ask Petch's father to meet with me.

463
00:37:03,240 --> 00:37:05,520
- Noted, sir.
- Please don't tell my dad.

464
00:37:06,960 --> 00:37:09,640
I will accept any punishment.

465
00:37:10,480 --> 00:37:11,960
But please.

466
00:37:12,760 --> 00:37:14,280
Don't inform my dad.

467
00:37:46,200 --> 00:37:47,960
Damn it!

468
00:37:48,040 --> 00:37:49,720
- Dam!
- Damn it!

469
00:37:49,800 --> 00:37:51,480
Dam, stop!

470
00:37:52,840 --> 00:37:54,440
What the hell are you doing?

471
00:37:54,520 --> 00:37:55,840
Petch.

472
00:37:55,920 --> 00:38:00,440
If Joe is above the school regulation,
then he should be under my fist!

473
00:38:00,520 --> 00:38:02,800
Is getting expelled worth it?

474
00:38:04,480 --> 00:38:05,400
Your hand

475
00:38:05,480 --> 00:38:07,240
is for music.

476
00:38:07,320 --> 00:38:09,080
It's not for punching Joe's face.

477
00:38:14,640 --> 00:38:15,640
Yes.

478
00:38:16,800 --> 00:38:17,880
You're right.

479
00:38:20,160 --> 00:38:22,120
I will express my anger

480
00:38:22,640 --> 00:38:24,280
with drums.

481
00:38:25,160 --> 00:38:27,280
- Joe is not worth it.
- Yes!

482
00:38:27,360 --> 00:38:28,920
That's what I'm talking about.

483
00:38:37,200 --> 00:38:38,240
Petch.

484
00:38:39,600 --> 00:38:40,440
What?

485
00:38:40,520 --> 00:38:42,960
The Rock Concert will be held this year.

486
00:38:44,200 --> 00:38:45,040
What's that?

487
00:38:45,840 --> 00:38:48,440
My friend sent me
the part-time job application link.

488
00:38:48,520 --> 00:38:51,120
"They're looking for backstage staff.

489
00:38:51,640 --> 00:38:53,800
Apply in person by the end of the day."

490
00:38:56,600 --> 00:38:58,960
Backstage staff.

491
00:38:59,840 --> 00:39:02,320
Which means
we can see the concert for free.

492
00:39:02,400 --> 00:39:04,000
- Right?
- Right.

493
00:39:04,080 --> 00:39:05,440
- Right?
- Right.

494
00:39:05,520 --> 00:39:07,320
Terrific!

495
00:39:07,400 --> 00:39:09,760
- Yes!
- Yes!

496
00:39:09,840 --> 00:39:11,040
Yes!

497
00:39:13,240 --> 00:39:14,080
What?

498
00:39:15,240 --> 00:39:16,440
I can't go.

499
00:39:18,320 --> 00:39:20,120
I haven't finished my clean-up duty.

500
00:39:21,360 --> 00:39:23,760
You go without me
or you won't make it in time.

501
00:39:24,360 --> 00:39:25,360
What?

502
00:39:25,880 --> 00:39:26,960
I can't.

503
00:39:29,200 --> 00:39:30,040
Listen, man.

504
00:39:30,560 --> 00:39:33,360
I will apply for you too.

505
00:39:33,440 --> 00:39:37,400
Don't worry, man.
You will be at The Rock Concert for sure.

506
00:39:38,160 --> 00:39:39,160
Later, man.

507
00:40:03,640 --> 00:40:05,400
- Hello.
- Hello.

508
00:40:05,480 --> 00:40:07,240
Hi, ladies. Where's Dao?

509
00:40:07,840 --> 00:40:09,400
She has already gone out.

510
00:40:10,440 --> 00:40:11,440
Already?

511
00:40:11,960 --> 00:40:15,400
Didn't she tell you
that she's going to buy a new piano?

512
00:40:35,280 --> 00:40:36,120
Hello?

513
00:40:36,200 --> 00:40:37,400
Dao.

514
00:40:38,200 --> 00:40:41,040
I told you I'd pick you up.
Why didn't you wait for me?

515
00:40:41,120 --> 00:40:42,800
I'm sorry. I forgot.

516
00:40:43,560 --> 00:40:44,960
<i>That's all right.</i>

517
00:40:45,040 --> 00:40:47,160
See you at the piano shop then.

518
00:40:47,240 --> 00:40:48,480
<i>Don't bother.</i>

519
00:40:48,560 --> 00:40:51,160
<i>You'll be joining dinner</i>
<i>with my parents anyway.</i>

520
00:40:51,240 --> 00:40:53,840
See you there. Goodbye.

521
00:40:59,320 --> 00:41:01,040
You're going to be my girlfriend.

522
00:41:02,480 --> 00:41:03,960
You can't get away from me.

523
00:41:17,400 --> 00:41:19,920
We hit the motorbike.

524
00:41:20,000 --> 00:41:21,880
I will go take a look, miss.

525
00:41:29,360 --> 00:41:30,320
Damn!

526
00:41:30,840 --> 00:41:32,400
The bumper is all scratched up.

527
00:41:32,960 --> 00:41:35,120
You punk! Watch where you're going!

528
00:41:35,200 --> 00:41:38,360
You should worry about him, not the car.

529
00:41:38,880 --> 00:41:40,920
You. Are you all right?

530
00:41:41,520 --> 00:41:42,760
I'm all right.

531
00:41:43,600 --> 00:41:44,440
But…

532
00:41:44,960 --> 00:41:47,680
I don't know
if I'll be able to afford the repairs.

533
00:41:52,240 --> 00:41:53,640
Please take this.

534
00:41:53,720 --> 00:41:55,920
Get a physical checkup too.

535
00:41:57,160 --> 00:41:59,960
Miss, he's the one who cut us off.

536
00:42:00,040 --> 00:42:02,200
At fault or not, he's still a human.

537
00:42:02,280 --> 00:42:05,000
It won't kill us to help him.
Kindness won't harm anyone.

538
00:42:06,040 --> 00:42:07,320
Here.

539
00:42:08,000 --> 00:42:10,680
Please accept this. I truly mean well.

540
00:42:11,920 --> 00:42:13,160
Thank you.

541
00:42:13,240 --> 00:42:14,200
Don't mention it.

542
00:42:14,800 --> 00:42:15,760
Uncle Kame.

543
00:42:15,840 --> 00:42:17,960
Please wait for the insurance agent here.

544
00:42:18,040 --> 00:42:19,040
All right, miss.

545
00:42:26,680 --> 00:42:28,360
Good afternoon.

546
00:42:28,960 --> 00:42:30,280
Oh, Ake. There you are!

547
00:42:31,440 --> 00:42:33,920
I bought you the famous mango sticky rice.

548
00:42:34,800 --> 00:42:37,640
We just want you to join our dinner.

549
00:42:37,720 --> 00:42:39,640
You don't have to bother.

550
00:42:39,720 --> 00:42:41,880
That doesn't bother me at all.

551
00:42:41,960 --> 00:42:45,880
Since both of you
are close friends with my uncle,

552
00:42:45,960 --> 00:42:49,240
I consider you two
as people I'm deeply indebted to.

553
00:42:49,920 --> 00:42:51,520
You really care for your elders.

554
00:42:51,600 --> 00:42:54,480
I hope your dessert
won't make Pen gain weight.

555
00:42:54,560 --> 00:42:56,280
- Honey.
- Don't worry, ma'am.

556
00:42:56,360 --> 00:42:59,520
I will take you out for some exercise.

557
00:42:59,600 --> 00:43:01,880
I will wait and see.

558
00:43:03,080 --> 00:43:06,800
You and Ake are two peas in a pod.

559
00:43:06,880 --> 00:43:10,560
I won't exercise alone.
I'll take Dao with me.

560
00:43:11,680 --> 00:43:13,720
Speaking of Dao,

561
00:43:14,520 --> 00:43:17,840
has she arrived home yet?

562
00:43:26,840 --> 00:43:29,320
Am I speaking to Ms. Natedao?

563
00:43:29,400 --> 00:43:30,560
Yes.

564
00:43:31,080 --> 00:43:34,280
The manager informed me
that you'll take a look at the pianos.

565
00:43:34,360 --> 00:43:35,480
This way, please.

566
00:43:43,920 --> 00:43:45,680
Please take your time.

567
00:43:45,760 --> 00:43:48,720
These pianos
all meet professional standards.

568
00:43:48,800 --> 00:43:51,920
They are all imported
from Europe and America.

569
00:43:52,000 --> 00:43:54,200
They're all perfect for your status.

570
00:43:55,280 --> 00:43:56,880
Can I have some privacy, please?

571
00:43:57,880 --> 00:43:59,600
Pardon me?

572
00:44:00,920 --> 00:44:02,120
I mean…

573
00:44:02,640 --> 00:44:04,920
Can I have some privacy to try the piano?

574
00:44:05,720 --> 00:44:08,080
I see. Of course.

575
00:44:20,200 --> 00:44:22,000
DAM. CLEAN-UP DUTY IS DONE.

576
00:44:22,080 --> 00:44:26,200
STOPPING TO WINDOW-SHOP SOME GUITARS
BEFORE HITTING NOODLES HOUSE.

577
00:44:47,920 --> 00:44:51,000
Please let me know when you're ready.

578
00:47:26,960 --> 00:47:29,360
I hope you don't mind that I join you.

579
00:47:33,600 --> 00:47:34,640
Wait.

580
00:47:55,040 --> 00:47:56,680
Music is not an emotional punching bag.

581
00:47:56,760 --> 00:47:58,520
In many parts of your life,

582
00:47:58,600 --> 00:48:00,280
<i>you might have no choice.</i>

583
00:48:01,320 --> 00:48:02,480
<i>But in this moment,</i>

584
00:48:03,080 --> 00:48:04,520
<i>you can make the choice.</i>

585
00:48:05,280 --> 00:48:08,080
NEXT EPISODE

586
00:48:08,160 --> 00:48:10,840
Dao is out of your league.

587
00:48:11,360 --> 00:48:12,840
Get lost.

588
00:48:13,440 --> 00:48:14,480
You absolute mongrel.

589
00:48:14,560 --> 00:48:17,120
I'm forbidding you
from seeing my daughter.

590
00:48:17,720 --> 00:48:20,480
Cross that line and your future is over.

591
00:48:36,720 --> 00:48:41,920
<i>I wish I knew if I ever crossed your mind</i>

592
00:48:42,880 --> 00:48:48,040
<i>I wish I knew if you heard the whisper</i>

593
00:48:48,600 --> 00:48:54,560
<i>For my heart is crying out my love</i>
<i>It's deep and true</i>

594
00:48:54,640 --> 00:48:59,560
<i>But never reaching you</i>

595
00:49:00,480 --> 00:49:05,440
<i>I know that it simply cannot be</i>

596
00:49:06,640 --> 00:49:11,360
<i>And I never want to cause you misery</i>

597
00:49:12,960 --> 00:49:18,360
<i>I'm just an ordinary man</i>
<i>Worth nothing at all</i>

598
00:49:19,240 --> 00:49:24,400
<i>And I never want to make</i>
<i>Your teardrops fall</i>

599
00:49:25,480 --> 00:49:29,960
<i>You are out of reach</i>

600
00:49:30,560 --> 00:49:36,600
<i>Is it a crime that I need you?</i>

601
00:49:37,840 --> 00:49:43,120
<i>Please let me know for sure</i>

602
00:49:43,200 --> 00:49:47,800
<i>That you're the one I've been waiting for</i>

603
00:49:48,600 --> 00:49:53,120
<i>How much longer can I bear this pain?</i>

604
00:49:54,760 --> 00:50:00,200
<i>How much longer must I wait in vain?</i>

605
00:50:00,280 --> 00:50:05,600
<i>I really don't know what move to make</i>

606
00:50:06,200 --> 00:50:11,920
<i>To end this heartache</i>
<i>And say that I love you</i>

607
00:50:40,680 --> 00:50:45,400
<i>You are out of reach</i>

608
00:50:45,480 --> 00:50:51,000
<i>Is it a crime that I need you?</i>

609
00:50:52,960 --> 00:50:57,000
<i>Please let me know for sure</i>

610
00:50:57,600 --> 00:51:00,920
<i>That you're the one I've been waiting for</i>

611
00:51:01,000 --> 00:51:02,760
Subtitle translation by: Sarunpon T.
